ACTOR Oros Mampofu and his girlfriend Bianca Carmichael are launching a book that’s a tribute to their daughter, Aarya. They will launch the book titled Amila’s Adventures on 19 February. It is named after Aarya’s second name, Amilamagcaga. Announcing the news, Oros said the book would also be for African girls around the world. He said they were eager to release the book. “It is with excitement that we announce that @bianca_carm and I will be launching a booklet in tribute to our little girl Aarya Amilamagcaga Glory and all the little African girls around the world. We have been waiting patiently and with great eagerness to finally come to this day because I’m sure you can imagine that this has been a project very dear to our hearts,” he wrote. ALSO READ : QV EVICTS HERSELF FROM BIG BROTHER! The actor said the launch would be on her daughter’s birthday weekend and they would have a special reading. “To make an early bird booking of the Amila’s Adventures booklet or enquire about anything regarding Aarya, reach us via DM on @aarya_mampofu (Instagram),” he wrote. He also thanked writer Rachel Ray Makutu, who co-wrote the book. “A big thank you to our co-writer @wraychelle for helping us make something so special and of course our precious daughter for inspiring us to make a change in our little way,” wrote Oros. Industry peers congratulated Oros, Bianca and Aarya on their new book. A post shared by Oros Mampofu (@oros_mampofu) 